        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10732",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan",
                        "name": "stefan",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Koopmanschap",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Additional info:\n\nThe request itself is being received by the receiving script. The headers arrive as they should. I added an extra header, and this is being displayed by the server.php script. The Content-length header contains the right amount for the test data being sent. Echo-ing the data inside Zend_Http_Client also displays that the data is correct when it is being sent.\n\nFor some reason though, the actual body of the POST message is not being recognized and parsed as $_POST data.\n\nOn a hunch, I just tried to see what are the contents of $HTTP_RAW_POST_DATA and this one is actually being filled. If this is a feature, then we need to document it I think. If this is a bug, we should fix it ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan",
                        "name": "stefan",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Koopmanschap",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-23T12:40:12.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-23T12:40:12.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10800",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I didn't test, but I'd bet this is because you do not set a 'Content-type' header in the request.\nPlease try to set an extra header: 'Content-type: application\/x-www-form-urlencoded' and see what happens.\n\nIn the new HTTP client (incubator) this is handeled automatically. If this is the case, I see no point in fixing the old client.\n\nLet me know how it goes.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-09T04:16:59.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-09T04:16:59.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10832",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan",
                        "name": "stefan",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Koopmanschap",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Wonderful, that indeed solves the issue. My knowledge of HTTP is clearly not good enough ;)",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=stefan",
                        "name": "stefan",
                        "displayName": "Stefan Koopmanschap",
